description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen within the Perinatal Mental Health Service for an effective and organised Administrator to join our friendly and dynamic Team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The post holder will provide a comprehensive clerical, administrative and secretarial service to the service and will be responsible for a variety of front of house activities and being a first point of contact for the service. In addition to this the post holder will be required to demonstrate appropriate computer literacy and data management skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The post holder will need to have a high level of personal and professional organisational skills, self-motivation and flexibility in approach and attitude. Excellent interpersonal and communication skills, both verbally and in writing will be essential along with the ability to work in a collaborative manner with a wide variety of Health and Social Care Professionals, service users and partner organisations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; English and/or Welsh speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameHelen McIntyreJob titleService Manager Adult MH Services North PowysEmail addresshelen.mcintyre1@wales.nhs.ukTelephone number07929781781Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
